<%@ Control Language="C#" Inherits="System.Web.Mvc.ViewUserControl<Insourcia.Psychotherapy.Model.FormData>" %>
<%@ Import Namespace="Insourcia.Psychotherapy.Model" %>

<h3 class="title">
       RIVERVALLEY AND AFFILIATES<br />
       ACCOUNTABLE DISCLOSURE TRACKING LOG
</h3>

<ul class="beginItem">
    <li>For each consumer, you are required to keep a log of all disclosures of PHI for non-TPO reasons for which you did not description of type of disclosure.  In addition, you need to provide a description of the PHI disclosed along with the names and titles to whom it was disclosed.</li>
    <li>Patient Name: <input type="text" name="AD0001T_NAME" class="inputTxt-max" /></li>
    <li>Medical Record Number: <input type="text" name="AD0002C_MEDICAL_RECORD_NUMBER" class="inputTxt-max" /></li>
    <li><table width="99%" border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="text_align">
          <tr>
            <td>Date Disclosed</td>
            <td>To Whom PHI Was Disclosed</td>
            <td>Address, if known</td>
            <td>Brief Description of PHI Disclosed</td>
            <td>Purpose of Disclosure</td>
            <td>Disclosed by Emp. Number, Cost Center or Full Name</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><input type="text" name="AD0003D_DATE_DISCLOSED" class="inputTxt" value="<%=Html.Encode(DateTime.Now.ToShortDateString()) %>" /></td>
            <td><input type="text" name="AD0004T_PHI_DISCLOSED" class="inputTxt" /></td>
            <td><input type="text" name="AD0005T_ADDRESS" class="inputTxt" /></td>
            <td><input type="text" name="AD0006T_BRIEF_DESCRIPTION_PHI" class="inputTxt" /></td>
            <td><input type="text" name="AD0007T_PURPOSE_DISCLOSURE" class="inputTxt" /></td>
            <td><input type="text" name="AD0008T_COST_CENTER_FULL_NAME" class="inputTxt" /></td>
          </tr>
       </table>
       </li>
    <li>Note: The company must retain documentation and tracking logs for each consumer for six (6) years from the date of its creation or the date when it last was in affect whichever is later.</li>
</ul>
